      "color": "#dbeafe",
      "description": "SLC20A2 and XPR1 directly regulate inorganic phosphate influx and efflux, while NAA60 loss secondarily reduces SLC20A2 surface abundance and phosphate uptake. Together these defects dysregulate phosphate handling in the brain microvascular environment and promote calcium-phosphate deposition.",
      "id": "Disrupted phosphate transport homeostasis",
      "is_orphan": false,
      "meta": {
        "biological_processes": [
          "phosphate ion transmembrane transport"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          {
            "reference": "PMID:32506582",
            "snippet": "Haploinsufficiency of SLC20A2, which encodes an inorganic phosphate importer, is a major cause of autosomal-dominant PFBC.",
            "supports": "SUPPORT"
          },
          {
            "reference": "PMID:25938945",
            "snippet": "These mutations alter phosphate export, implicating XPR1 and phosphate homeostasis in PFBC.",
            "supports": "SUPPORT"
          },
          {
            "reference": "PMID:38480682",
            "snippet": "In cells, loss of NAA60 caused reduced surface levels of SLC20A2 and a reduction in extracellular phosphate uptake.",
            "supports": "SUPPORT"
          }
        ],
        "evidence_count": 3,
